The original biubug6/Pytorch_Retinaface implementation
(https://github.com/biubug6/Pytorch_Retinaface) is the upstream prior art
under the MIT License (Copyright (c) 2019).

py-feat's adaptations:
- ResNet34 backbone via torchvision instead of yakhyo's vendored copy
- Module renamed `body` (was `fx`) for the backbone wrapper
- Heads exposed as ClassHead/BboxHead/LandmarkHead each holding an internal
  ModuleList of 1x1 convs
- Batched, on-device postprocess: priors cached per (H, W, device), single
  call to torchvision.ops.batched_nms across the entire batch
- HuggingFace weights distributed at https://huggingface.co/py-feat/retinaface_r34
  (state_dict remapped from yakhyo's layout via scripts/prepare_retinaface_r34.py)

